article.headline: Pacific 71, CS Bakersfield 44
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Sam Willard had 21 points and nine rebounds to lead Pacific to a 71-44 victory against Cal State Bakersfield on Saturday. Freshman Stephon Lamar had a career-high 13 points for the Tigers (16-8). Trent Blakley had 12 points and Santwan Latunde 10 for Cal State Bakersfield (6-18). Pacific's defense never allowed the Roadrunners to establish an offensive rhythm. Bakersfield was just 13 of 41 (31.7 percent) from the floor and had just three assists.
